#circuitbreakersg day 44

Did I say that I love flowers? 🤓
.
.
.
Yes I love 🌸 🌺 so much so that I would eat them! 🤣 .
.
.
Made pasta with edible flowers and some herbs for dinner tonight, and boy, was it time-consuming! Not recommended for a weeknight-after-work, made-from-scratch kinda dinner. If not for the fact that the edible flowers which I got could only last a few days, I would have preferred to make these pasta over the weekend instead.
.
.
.
But, I’m not complaining because I loved the process of making these pretty pasta 😍 which I found very therapeutic! 😇 .
.
.
And I’m grateful for having these pretty and tasty pasta for dinner tonight! 💗 #gratitudediary
.
.
.

@ainz_gourmet 😂😂 thank you, you are so kind! I just didn’t want the flowers to go to waste 😜
@28nankinstreet I hear you... I would have just eaten the flowers with a simpler dish and buy again for the noodles next time 😅😂

Salute 1: with the beautiful dish using edible flowers, 
Salute 2: cook from scratch,
Salute 3: weeknight??!!!! So creative🌸 and determined 💪🏼 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼
Your food looks amazing! Handmade pasta is the best! 🍝🍝😝😝
@kaitsdish thanks! I need more practice but yes am getting the hang of it! 😊😁
Amazing noodles! You are getting so good at it! 😍👍
Omg that pasta is so beautiful. Homemade pasta is so good 😍😍
